      "span_text": "Thus, the data from this discovery proteomics study, together with previously published data [CITATION_1] , support the postulate that in response to ozoneinduced oxidative stress there is an increase in total protein oxidation and this reflects decreases in proteins involved in redox balance and increases in proteins involved in protein modification and metabolism."
